    • Constructor Detail

      • PressureUnit

        public PressureUnit(MassUnit massUnit,
            LengthUnit lengthUnit,
            TimeUnit timeUnit,
            String nameKey,
            String abbreviationKey,
            UnitSystem unitSystem)
        Construct a pressure unit from mass, length and time units.
        Parameters:
        massUnit - the unit of mass for the pressure unit, e.g., kilogram
        lengthUnit - the unit of length for the pressure unit, e.g., meter
        timeUnit - the unit of time for the pressure unit, e.g., second
        nameKey - the key to the locale file for the long name of the unit
        abbreviationKey - the key to the locale file for the abbreviation of the unit
        unitSystem - the unit system, e.g. SI or Imperial

      • PressureUnit

        public PressureUnit(ForceUnit forceUnit,
            AreaUnit areaUnit,
            String nameKey,
            String abbreviationKey,
            UnitSystem unitSystem)
        Construct a pressure unit from force and area units.
        Parameters:
        forceUnit - the unit of force for the pressure unit, e.g., Newton
        areaUnit - the unit of area for the pressure unit, e.g., m^2
        nameKey - the key to the locale file for the long name of the unit
        abbreviationKey - the key to the locale file for the abbreviation of the unit
        unitSystem - the unit system, e.g. SI or Imperial

      • PressureUnit

        public PressureUnit(String nameKey,
            String abbreviationKey,
            UnitSystem unitSystem,
            PressureUnit referenceUnit,
            double conversionFactorToReferenceUnit)
        Build a unit with a conversion factor to another unit.
        Parameters:
        nameKey - the key to the locale file for the long name of the unit
        abbreviationKey - the key to the locale file for the abbreviation of the unit
        unitSystem - the unit system, e.g. SI or Imperial
        referenceUnit - the unit to convert to
        conversionFactorToReferenceUnit - multiply a value in this unit by the factor to convert to the given reference unit
